On 2/14/03 12:49 PM, "mikeprather(-at-)att.net" <mikeprather(-at-)att.net> wrote:

> I quote; "Synthetic engine oil was designed for watercooled engines which, of
> course, use water to cool the engine. Aircooled VW's otoh, use air and oil to
> cool the engine.Synthetic oil, by nature resists heat in an effort to prevent
> thermal breakdown of the oil. Engine oil in an aircooled VW acts as both a
> lubricant and a coolant. When synthetic oil is used in an aircooled VW, the
> oil 
> resists heat heat generated by the engine, resulting in an increase of the
> cylinder head temp..."

Apparently they are unaware of the following:

- Mobil introduced Mobil 1 in 1976
- Porsche has approved the use of synthetic oil in its engines since 1980
- Porsche's have been "factory filled" with Mobil 1 since August 1992.
- Porsche 911's were air cooled until the 1998 model year

> Just some food for thought on friday, feel free to pick apart their reasoning
> (or mine if necesary).

